We now allow customers to enter an arbitrary Subversion path, and manage Subversion read and commit privileges for it. For instance, say I start with {{/AP}} readable by {{developers}}:

!ap.png!

This yields the {{authz}} section:

{code}
[/AP]
@users =
@developers = r
@_no-one-at-all = r
_bamboo-svn-user = r
{code}

No I:
 - Go to the "Add a Modify commit permissions for an arbitrary path:" section and add {{/AP/trunk}} to override permissions for trunk.
 - On the next screen, grant the {{foo}} group read permission:

!apfoo.png!

The config file now looks like this:

{noformat}
[/AP]
@users =
@developers = r
@_no-one-at-all = r
_bamboo-svn-user = r
[/AP/trunk]
@users =
@_no-one-at-all = r
@foo = r
_bamboo-svn-user = r
{noformat}

The {{/AP/trunk}} path *should* inherit the {{@developer = r}} permission, but doesn't. Everyone not in the {{foo}} group is locked out.

